verbs.description: deblock (third-person singular simple present deblocks, present participle deblocking, simple past and past participle deblocked)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To unblock; remove a blockage from.
(transitive, computing) To separate the logical records that have been combined into a physical block for storage.
(transitive, computing) To process (digital video) so as to remove block-shaped artifacts of encoding.
